10/05/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A memorial with the names of 521 children killed during the Sarajevo siege was unveiled on Sunday (May 9th) in the city. 
Relatives, local officials and members of the public attended the ceremony, held on Europe Day. 
They laid white roses in front of the monument in memory of children who lost their lives in the 1992-1995 conflict. 
Victims ranged in age from newborn to 18. 
In all, about 1,500 children are believed to have been killed in the fighting. 
(BHRT, Nezavisne Novine, Fena, AFP - 09/05/10)
